没错，就是电影《哥斯拉》。

324
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:12,080
He's a monster.
他是个怪物。

325
00:14:12,080 --> 00:14:13,080
And he's out of control.
而且他失控了。

326
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:15,400
He's out of control.
他失控了。

327
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:21,560
And a bride who's so obsessed with her wedding that nothing else is important, she is a bridezilla.
一个对自己的婚礼痴迷到其他一切都不重要的新娘，就是新娘怪兽。

328
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:26,560
Now it's a very big thing for a woman, right, for her wedding to be nice and perfect and
对女人来说，婚礼要办得漂亮完美，这是件大事，对吧？

329
00:14:26,560 --> 00:14:27,560
everything.
一切。

330
00:14:27,560 --> 00:14:28,560
Do you think guys are more relaxed in this sense?
你觉得男人在这方面更放松吗？

331
00:14:28,560 --> 00:14:29,560
I don't know.
我不知道。

332
00:14:29,560 --> 00:14:32,240
I think it depends on the guy, as always.
我觉得这因人而异，和往常一样。

333
00:14:32,240 --> 00:14:36,320
There are some people who want to be very involved, and some people who don't care.
有些人想积极参与，有些人则不在乎。

334
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:41,960
But in general, I think men are less worried about the details.
但总的来说，我认为男人不太担心细节。

335
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:44,040
Just as long as there's a wedding, it's fine.
只要有婚礼就行，没问题。

336
00:14:44,040 --> 00:14:45,040
Exactly.
没错。

337
00:14:45,040 --> 00:14:49,200
Although a lot of men, when the wedding actually happens, start to get very nervous.
不过很多男人在婚礼真正举行时，会开始变得非常紧张。

338
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:52,000
But kind of like having doubts, maybe cold feet.
但有点像产生怀疑，也许是临阵退缩。

339
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:53,400
Yes, cold feet.
是的，临阵退缩。

340
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:54,400
Like should I get married?
比如“我该结婚吗？”

341
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:56,440
Should I not get married?
“我不该结婚吗？”

342
00:14:56,440 --> 00:15:00,000
I think it's very interesting because you see this in movies a lot.
我觉得这很有趣，因为你在电影里经常看到这种情况。

343
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:07,360
And I've always wondered how often or how common is it for a guy or a girl to say no
我一直想知道，一个男人或女人在婚礼已经开始时说“不”或离开，这种情况有多常见？

344
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:10,960
or to leave a wedding when it has already started.
或者离开已经开始的婚礼。

345
00:15:10,960 --> 00:15:14,960
Because you know, you have invited all these people, all these friends and family, maybe
因为你邀请了所有人，所有朋友和家人，也许

346
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:18,840
people came from different countries, and food is paid for, venue.
有人从不同国家赶来，食物和场地都付了钱。

347
00:15:18,840 --> 00:15:21,960
You spend so much money on a wedding and for you to say no.
你在婚礼上花了这么多钱，然后你说“不”。

348
00:15:21,960 --> 00:15:23,200
I don't know how common it is.
我不知道这有多常见。

349
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:28,640
It's very common in movies, but I really don't know anyone who's experienced this.
这在电影里很常见，但我真的不认识经历过这种事的人。

350
00:15:28,640 --> 00:15:30,600
I don't either, actually, now that you bring it up.
说实话，你一提起来，我也不认识。

351
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:32,360
So maybe we could talk about this.
所以也许我们可以聊聊这个。

352
00:15:32,360 --> 00:15:34,040
Is this common in your country?
这在你们国家常见吗？

353
00:15:34,040 --> 00:15:36,680
First of all, do people spend a lot of money on weddings?
首先，人们在婚礼上花很多钱吗？

354
00:15:36,680 --> 00:15:41,440
And second of all, have you ever heard of someone actually leaving the wedding before
其次，你听说过有人在婚礼结束前离开吗？

355
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:42,440
they finished?
在结束前？

356
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:44,160
Yes, during the ceremony.
是的，在仪式期间。

357
00:15:44,160 --> 00:15:45,160
Not before, during.
不是之前，是期间。

358
00:15:45,160 --> 00:15:46,160
During the ceremony.
在仪式期间。

359
00:15:46,160 --> 00:15:48,280
So our website is EnglishPod.com.
所以我们的网站是 EnglishPod.com。

360
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:49,480
And we hope to see you there.
我们希望能在那里见到你。

361
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:50,480
Until next time.
下次见。

362
00:15:50,480 --> 00:16:18,480
Bye.
再见。
